        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Use $2\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta$. $\\sin\\theta=1/3, \\cos\\theta=\\sqrt{8}/3 = 2\\sqrt{2}/3$. Result $= 2(1/3)(2\\sqrt{2}/3) = 4\\sqrt{2}/9$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Evaluate $\\arctan(\\tan(3\\pi/4))$.",
        "options": ["$-\\pi/4$", "$\\pi/4$", "$3\\pi/4$", "$-3\\pi/4$"],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$\\tan(3\\pi/4) = -1$. $\\arctan(-1) = -\\pi/4$ (must be in $(-\\pi/2, \\pi/2)$)."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Simplify $\\sin(x + y) + \\sin(x - y)$.",
        "options": ["$2\\sin x \\cos y$", "$2\\cos x \\sin y$", "$2\\sin x \\sin y$", "$2\\cos x \\cos y$"],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Expansion: $(\\sin x \\cos y + \\cos x \\sin y) + (\\sin x \\cos y - \\cos x \\sin y) = 2\\sin x \\cos y$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "If $\\tan x = 1/2$ and $\\tan y = 1/3$, find $\\tan(x+y)$.",
