        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$\\sin x = \\sqrt{3}/2$ (positive in $[0,\\pi]$), giving $x = \\pi/3, 2\\pi/3$."
      },
      {
        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Solve $2\\sin x - \\sqrt{3} = 0$ for $x \\in [0, 2\\pi)$.",
